articles.author: Jenni Reid
articles.title: Europe stocks open higher, head for best week since March after central bank pauses - CNBC
articles.description: European markets opened higher Friday, continuing the week's rally as investors assess the interest rate outlook.
articles.content:
European stock markets were cautiously higher on Friday, rounding off a weekly rally powered by a series of solid earnings and a perceived dovish tilt by central banks.
